==English==
{{wikipediapar|Granfalloon}}
===Etymology===
Coined by [[w:Kurt Vonnegut|Kurt Vonnegut]] in the 1963 science fiction novel, [[w:Cat's Cradle|Cat's Cradle]], in which Vonnegut described the term as referencing "a proud and meaningless association of human beings"; later adopted by market researchers and social scientists

===Noun===
'''granfalloon''' (''plural'': '''[[granfalloons]]''')
# A group of two or more people who imagine or are manipulated to believe they share a connection based on some circumstance of little or no real significance.